    "long_instructions": "# Do This\r\n1. Create three functions called `collect_paint`, `paint_a_row`, and `move_to_next_row`.\r\n#\r\n2. `collect_paint` should use a `while painter.is_on_bucket` loop.\r\n#\r\n3. `paint_a_row` should use a `while painter.can_move` loop, along with `paint()` and `move()`.\r\n#\r\n4. `move_to_next_row` should use the `turn_left()` or `turn_right()` and `move()` methods.\r\n    - Hint: Think about which direction the Painter will need to turn and move depending on whether it is on the far left or far right side of the grid.\r\n5. Use all three functions together to paint each row of the Neighborhood.\r\n#\r\n6. Run your code and observe how the Painter collects paint, paints a row, and then moves to the next row.\r\n ",
